{"overview":"This piece is cast in a modified ternary/rondo form in C# minor, characterized by a pervasive modal mixture that darkens the harmony through persistent ♭VII and borrowed Phrygian/natural-minor inflections throughout. Its most distinctive feature is the extended development-like section (bars 28–42) that prolongs G# minor as a dominant region through chromatic voice-leading and ornamental figuration before a dramatically prepared recapitulation.","cross_piece_tags":["ternary","modal_mixture","pedal_point","lyrical","melancholic","dramatic","chromatic_mediant","counterpoint"]}
